                        <desc><persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1853">Leontius</persName> left his
                            monastery in the same manner as his fellow monastic <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2032">Qashish</persName> to travel
                            alone to the eastern, southern, and western regions in the capacity of a
                            wandering monk (aksnāyutā) for many years, while both let their hair
                            grow long in a worldly fashion, lest they be honored as monks. </desc>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/830"/><citedRange unit="p">443</citedRange></bibl>
